    "2020) Vertex-level information maximization O N 2 Medium 2020 Low Capturing vertex information, efficient Ignoring the global information Table 9 (continued) Methods Reason for preference Computational Efficiency Scalability Year Popularity Plus aspects Minus aspects CGIPool (Pang et al. 2021) Coarsening and information maximization O N 2 Medium 2021 Medium Capturing coarsened graph information efficient Computationally expensive, limited interpretability Table 9 (continued) To further compare the performance of global pooling, hierarchical pooling methods, and basic GNN methods (GCN (Kipf and Welling 2016), GraphSAGE (Hamilton et al. 2017), and GAT (Veličković et al. 2017)) on the benchmark datasets, we conducted comparative analyses on the PROTEINS, MUTAG, NCI1, and DD datasets.",
    "Table 10 summarizes the accuracy of representative graph pooling methods on these datasets.",
    "The following points can be observed from these comparison experiments:",
    "• Limitations of GNN methods: Compared to models incorporating graph pooling techniques, traditional GNN methods tend to ignore the hierarchical structure information of the graph during node aggregation, which leads to their relatively poor performance in classification tasks."
